Let ${\rm f}:\left[a, b\right]\to\mathbb{R}$ be twice differentiable, and suppose $$\lim_{x\to a^{+}}
\frac{{\rm f}\left(x\right) - {\rm f}\left(a\right)}{x - a}
=
\lim_{x\to b^{-}}\frac{{\rm f}\left(x\right) - {\rm f}\left(b\right)}{x - b}
=0
$$ Show that there exists $\xi \in \left(a, b\right)$ such that
$\displaystyle{%
\left\vert\vphantom{\Large A}\,{\rm f}''\left(\xi\right)\right\vert
\geq
\frac{4\left\vert\vphantom{\Large A}%
\,{\rm f}\left(a\right) - {\rm f}\left(b\right)\right\vert}
{\left(b - a\right)^{2}}}$. I don't know how to start. Any hints ?.

I have a dynamical system whose state is a vector $\mathbf{y}\in \mathbf{R}^m$. The vectors $\mathbf{y},\dot{\mathbf{y}},\ddot{\mathbf{y}}\in \mathbf{R}^m$ relate to the vectors $\mathbf{z},\dot{\mathbf{z}},\ddot{\mathbf{z}}\in \mathbf{R}^n$ through the transformations
\begin{align}
\mathbf{y}&=g(\mathbf{z})\\
\dot{\mathbf{y}}&=J(\mathbf{z})\dot{\mathbf{z}}\\
\ddot{\mathbf{y}}&=J(\mathbf{z})\ddot{\mathbf{z}} + \dot{J}(\mathbf{z})\dot{\mathbf{z}}
\end{align}
where $J$ is the Jacobian matrix of the nonlinear transformation $g$. What are the entries of $\dot{J}(\mathbf{z})$? For example, if $J_{ij}=\frac{\partial y_i}{\partial z_j}=a\sin(z_j)$, then what is $\dot{J}_{ij}$? (There is a similar but unanswered question here .)
